  384   void mul_wide_u32(uint32_T in0, uint32_T in1, uint32_T *ptrOutBitsHi, uint32_T
  385                     *ptrOutBitsLo)
  386   {
  387     uint32_T outBitsLo;
  388     uint32_T in0Lo;
  389     uint32_T in0Hi;
  390     uint32_T in1Lo;
  391     uint32_T in1Hi;
  392     uint32_T productHiLo;
  393     uint32_T productLoHi;
  394     in0Hi = in0 >> 16U;
  395     in0Lo = in0 & 65535U;
  396     in1Hi = in1 >> 16U;
  397     in1Lo = in1 & 65535U;
  398     productHiLo = in0Hi * in1Lo;
  399     productLoHi = in0Lo * in1Hi;
  400     in0Lo *= in1Lo;
  401     in1Lo = 0U;
  402     outBitsLo = (productLoHi << 16U) + in0Lo;
  403     if (outBitsLo < in0Lo) {
  404       in1Lo = 1U;
  405     }
  406   
  407     in0Lo = outBitsLo;
  408     outBitsLo += productHiLo << 16U;
  409     if (outBitsLo < in0Lo) {
  410       in1Lo++;
  411     }
  412   
  413     *ptrOutBitsHi = (((productLoHi >> 16U) + (productHiLo >> 16U)) + in0Hi * in1Hi)
  414       + in1Lo;
  415     *ptrOutBitsLo = outBitsLo;
  416   }

  418   uint32_T mul_u32_u32_u32_sr31(uint32_T a, uint32_T b)
  419   {
  420     uint32_T u32_chi;
  421     uint32_T u32_clo;
  422     mul_wide_u32(a, b, &u32_chi, &u32_clo);
  423     u32_clo = u32_chi << 1U | u32_clo >> 31U;
  424     return u32_clo;

  427   uint32_T div_nzp_repeat_u32(uint32_T numerator, uint32_T denominator, uint32_T
  428     nRepeatSub)
  429   {
  430     uint32_T quotient;
  431     uint32_T iRepeatSub;
  432     boolean_T numeratorExtraBit;
  433     quotient = numerator / denominator;
  434     numerator %= denominator;
  435     for (iRepeatSub = 0U; iRepeatSub < nRepeatSub; iRepeatSub++) {
  436       numeratorExtraBit = (numerator >= 2147483648U);
  437       numerator <<= 1U;
  438       quotient <<= 1U;
  439       if (numeratorExtraBit || (numerator >= denominator)) {
  440         quotient++;
  441         numerator -= denominator;
  442       }
  443     }
  444   
  445     return quotient;
  446   }

  448   uint32_T div_nzp_u32_near(uint32_T numerator, uint32_T denominator)
  449   {
  450     uint32_T tempAbsQuotient;
  451     tempAbsQuotient = numerator / denominator;
  452     numerator %= denominator;
  453     if ((numerator > 2147483647U) || ((numerator << 1U) >= denominator)) {
  454       tempAbsQuotient++;
  455     }
  456   
  457     return tempAbsQuotient;
  458   }

  460   uint16_T look1_iu16lu32n16_binlcse(uint16_T u0, const uint16_T bp0[], const
  461     uint16_T table[], uint32_T maxIndex)
  462   {
  463     uint16_T y;
  464     uint32_T frac;
  465     uint32_T iRght;
  466     uint32_T iLeft;
  467   
  468     /* Lookup 1-D
  469        Search method: 'binary'
  470        Use previous index: 'off'
  471        Interpolation method: 'Linear'
  472        Extrapolation method: 'Clip'
  473        Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'
  474        Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'
  475        Rounding mode: 'simplest'
  476      */
  477     /* Prelookup - Index and Fraction
  478        Index Search method: 'binary'
  479        Extrapolation method: 'Clip'
  480        Use previous index: 'off'
  481        Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'
  482        Remove protection against out-of-range input in generated code: 'off'
  483        Rounding mode: 'simplest'
  484      */
  485     if (u0 <= bp0[0U]) {
  486       iLeft = 0U;
  487       frac = 0U;
  488     } else if (u0 < bp0[maxIndex]) {
  489       /* Binary Search */
  490       frac = maxIndex >> 1U;
  491       iLeft = 0U;
  492       iRght = maxIndex;
  493       while (iRght - iLeft > 1U) {
  494         if (u0 < bp0[frac]) {
  495           iRght = frac;
  496         } else {
  497           iLeft = frac;
  498         }
  499   
  500         frac = (iRght + iLeft) >> 1U;
  501       }
  502   
  503       frac = ((uint32_T)(uint16_T)((uint32_T)u0 - bp0[iLeft]) << 16) / (uint16_T)
  504         ((uint32_T)bp0[iLeft + 1U] - bp0[iLeft]);
  505     } else {
  506       iLeft = maxIndex - 1U;
  507       frac = 65536U;
  508     }
  509   
  510     /* Interpolation 1-D
  511        Interpolation method: 'Linear'
  512        Use last breakpoint for index at or above upper limit: 'off'

  902   void sMultiWordMul(const uint32_T u1[], int32_T n1, const uint32_T u2[], int32_T
  903                      n2, uint32_T y[], int32_T n)
  904   {
  905     int32_T i;
  906     int32_T j;
  907     int32_T k;
  908     int32_T nj;
  909     uint32_T u1i;
  910     uint32_T yk;
  911     uint32_T a1;
  912     uint32_T a0;
  913     uint32_T b1;
  914     uint32_T w10;
  915     uint32_T w01;
  916     uint32_T cb;
  917     boolean_T isNegative1;
  918     boolean_T isNegative2;
  919     uint32_T cb1;
  920     uint32_T cb2;
  921     isNegative1 = ((u1[n1 - 1] & 2147483648U) != 0U);
  922     isNegative2 = ((u2[n2 - 1] & 2147483648U) != 0U);
  923     cb1 = 1U;
  924   
  925     /* Initialize output to zero */
  926     for (k = 0; k < n; k++) {
  927       y[k] = 0U;
  928     }
  929   
  930     for (i = 0; i < n1; i++) {
  931       cb = 0U;
  932       u1i = u1[i];
  933       if (isNegative1) {
  934         u1i = ~u1i + cb1;
  935         cb1 = u1i < cb1 ? 1U : 0U;
  936       }
  937   
  938       a1 = u1i >> 16U;
  939       a0 = u1i & 65535U;
  940       cb2 = 1U;
  941       k = n - i;
  942       nj = n2 <= k ? n2 : k;
  943       k = i;
  944       for (j = 0; j < nj; j++) {
  945         yk = y[k];
  946         u1i = u2[j];
  947         if (isNegative2) {
  948           u1i = ~u1i + cb2;
  949           cb2 = u1i < cb2 ? 1U : 0U;
  950         }
  951   
  952         b1 = u1i >> 16U;
  953         u1i &= 65535U;
  954         w10 = a1 * u1i;
  955         w01 = a0 * b1;
  956         yk += cb;
  957         cb = yk < cb ? 1U : 0U;
  958         u1i *= a0;
  959         yk += u1i;
  960         cb += yk < u1i ? 1U : 0U;
  961         u1i = w10 << 16U;
  962         yk += u1i;
  963         cb += yk < u1i ? 1U : 0U;
  964         u1i = w01 << 16U;
  965         yk += u1i;
  966         cb += yk < u1i ? 1U : 0U;
  967         y[k] = yk;
  968         cb += w10 >> 16U;
  969         cb += w01 >> 16U;
  970         cb += a1 * b1;
  971         k++;
  972       }
  973   
  974       if (k < n) {
  975         y[k] = cb;
  976       }
  977     }
  978   
  979     /* Apply sign */
  980     if (isNegative1 != isNegative2) {
  981       cb = 1U;
  982       for (k = 0; k < n; k++) {
  983         yk = ~y[k] + cb;
  984         y[k] = yk;
  985         cb = yk < cb ? 1U : 0U;
  986       }
  987     }
  988   }

 1070   void uMultiWordShr(const uint32_T u1[], int32_T n1, uint32_T n2, uint32_T y[],
 1071                      int32_T n)
 1072   {
 1073     int32_T nb;
 1074     int32_T i;
 1075     uint32_T yi;
 1076     uint32_T u1i;
 1077     int32_T nc;
 1078     uint32_T nr;
 1079     uint32_T nl;
 1080     int32_T i1;
 1081     nb = (int32_T)(n2 >> 5);
 1082     i = 0;
 1083     if (nb < n1) {
 1084       nc = n + nb;
 1085       if (nc > n1) {
 1086         nc = n1;
 1087       }
 1088   
 1089       nr = n2 - ((uint32_T)nb << 5);
 1090       if (nr > 0U) {
 1091         nl = 32U - nr;
 1092         u1i = u1[nb];
 1093         for (i1 = nb + 1; i1 < nc; i1++) {
 1094           yi = u1i >> nr;
 1095           u1i = u1[i1];
 1096           y[i] = u1i << nl | yi;
 1097           i++;
 1098         }
 1099   
 1100         yi = u1i >> nr;
 1101         if (nc < n1) {
 1102           yi |= u1[nc] << nl;
 1103         }
 1104   
 1105         y[i] = yi;
 1106         i++;
 1107       } else {
 1108         for (i1 = nb; i1 < nc; i1++) {
 1109           y[i] = u1[i1];
 1110           i++;
 1111         }
 1112       }

 1290   /*
 1291    * Set which subrates need to run this base step (base rate always runs).
 1292    * This function must be called prior to calling the model step function
 1293    * in order to "remember" which rates need to run this base step.  The
 1294    * buffering of events allows for overlapping preemption.
 1295    */
 1296   void E33_VCU_simulink_SetEventsForThisBaseStep(boolean_T *eventFlags)
 1297   {
 1298     /* Task runs when its counter is zero, computed via rtmStepTask macro */
 1299     eventFlags[1] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 1));
 1300     eventFlags[2] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 2));
 1301     eventFlags[3] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 3));
 1302     eventFlags[4] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 4));
 1303     eventFlags[5] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 5));
 1304     eventFlags[6] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 6));
 1305     eventFlags[7] = ((boolean_T)rtmStepTask(E33_VCU_simulink_M, 7));
 1306   }
 1307   
 1308   /*
 1309    *   This function updates active task flag for each subrate
 1310    * and rate transition flags for tasks that exchange data.
 1311    * The function assumes rate-monotonic multitasking scheduler.
 1312    * The function must be called at model base rate so that
 1313    * the generated code self-manages all its subrates and rate
 1314    * transition flags.
 1315    */
 1316   static void rate_monotonic_scheduler(void)
 1317   {
 1318     /* To ensure a deterministic data transfer between two rates,
 1319      * data is transferred at the priority of a fast task and the frequency
 1320      * of the slow task.  The following flags indicate when the data transfer
 1321      * happens.  That is, a rate interaction flag is set true when both rates
 1322      * will run, and false otherwise.
 1323      */
 1324   
 1325     /* tid 3 shares data with slower tid rates: 4, 5, 6 */
 1326     if (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[3] == 0) {
 1327       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.RateInteraction.TID3_4 =
 1328         (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[4] == 0);
 1329       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.RateInteraction.TID3_5 =
 1330         (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[5] == 0);
 1331       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.RateInteraction.TID3_6 =
 1332         (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[6] == 0);
 1333     }
 1334   
 1335     /* Compute which subrates run during the next base time step.  Subrates
 1336      * are an integer multiple of the base rate counter.  Therefore, the subtask
 1337      * counter is reset when it reaches its limit (zero means run).
 1338      */
 1339     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[1])++;
 1340     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[1]) > 1) {/* Sample time: [0.001s, 0.0s] */
 1341       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[1] = 0;
 1342     }
 1343   
 1344     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2])++;
 1345     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2]) > 9) {/* Sample time: [0.005s, 0.0s] */
 1346       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[2] = 0;
 1347     }
 1348   
 1349     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[3])++;
 1350     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[3]) > 19) {/* Sample time: [0.01s, 0.0s] */
 1351       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[3] = 0;
 1352     }
 1353   
 1354     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[4])++;
 1355     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[4]) > 39) {/* Sample time: [0.02s, 0.0s] */
 1356       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[4] = 0;
 1357     }
 1358   
 1359     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[5])++;
 1360     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[5]) > 99) {/* Sample time: [0.05s, 0.0s] */
 1361       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[5] = 0;
 1362     }
 1363   
 1364     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[6])++;
 1365     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[6]) > 199) {/* Sample time: [0.1s, 0.0s] */
 1366       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[6] = 0;
 1367     }
 1368   
 1369     (E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[7])++;
 1370     if ((E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[7]) > 999) {/* Sample time: [0.5s, 0.0s] */
 1371       E33_VCU_simulink_M->Timing.TaskCounters.TID[7] = 0;
 1372     }
 1373   }

 1375   real32_T rt_roundf_snf(real32_T u)
 1376   {
 1377     real32_T y;
 1378     if ((real32_T)fabs(u) < 8.388608E+6F) {
 1379       if (u >= 0.5F) {
 1380         y = (real32_T)floor(u + 0.5F);
 1381       } else if (u > -0.5F) {
 1382         y = u * 0.0F;
 1383       } else {
 1384         y = (real32_T)ceil(u - 0.5F);
 1385       }
 1386     } else {
 1387       y = u;
 1388     }
 1389   
 1390     return y;
 1391   }
 1392   
 1393   real_T rt_roundd_snf(real_T u)
 1394   {
 1395     real_T y;
 1396     if (fabs(u) < 4.503599627370496E+15) {
 1397       if (u >= 0.5) {
 1398         y = floor(u + 0.5);
 1399       } else if (u > -0.5) {
 1400         y = u * 0.0;
 1401       } else {
 1402         y = ceil(u - 0.5);
 1403       }
 1404     } else {
 1405       y = u;
 1406     }
 1407   
 1408     return y;
 1409   }

 1411   /* Function for Chart: '<S169>/LED' */
 1412   static real_T E33_VCU_simulink_GetDutyCyc(real_T elapsed_sec, real_T period)
 1413   {
 1414     real_T DutyCyc;
 1415   
 1416     /* MATLAB Function 'GetDutyCyc': '<S194>:9' */
 1417     /* '<S194>:9:2' */
 1418     DutyCyc = sin((elapsed_sec / period + 0.75) * 6.2831853071795862) * 25.0 +
 1419       25.0;
 1420   
 1421     /* Note: sin in rad */
 1422     return DutyCyc;
 1423   }
